	<a href="http://computerworld.com/hardwaretopics/hardware/story/0,10801,71665,00.html">IBM nets its biggest supercomputer deal yet - Computerworld</a>.&nbsp; The IBM order for the National Centers for Environmental Protection.&nbsp; The system will be built up in stages, achieving 100 TFLOPS by 2009.  IT starts with 42TB of storage in a cluster of 44 IBM eServer p690 servers.   That gets to 7.3 TFLOPS.  The system will occupy a room roughly the size of a basketball court and will be used remotely by the customer.<br>
