	<div class="posts">
	<a name="86402224">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h3>Available storage servers</h3><a href="http://computerworld.com/hardwaretopics/hardware/server/story/0,10801,76915,00.html">Dell, IBM and Sun to deliver InfiniBand servers - Computerworld</a>.&nbsp; InfiniBand technology, promises the ability to connect servers and storage systems in a data center at speeds from 2.5GB/sec. to 30GB/sec. vs. the roughly 1GB/sec. for existing Peripheral Component Interconnect. technology. <br /><br />It appears that the actual transfer rates are lower than that, but using 2GBs and faster connections will support bigger, faster bursts from storage systems.<br>
